The deployment(s) describe which equipment is deployed, during which time period, and in which configuration in the course of generating observations. A Deployment can describe any period of time (equipment could be deployed for less than a day, e.g. a mobile sensor deployed in the field, or it could be deployed for many years.) A defining characteristic of the Deployment is that the configuration described in the Deployment remains, by-and-large, unchanged for the duration of the deployment. If the configuration changes, then a new Deployment must be recorded.

XML encodings of WMDR shall be well formed XML documents (syntactically correct). A well-formed XML document conforms to the XML specification. (https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/ )
XML encodings of WMDR shall validate against the WMDR XML Schema (xsd).
This requirements class contains a set of general rules concerning the encoding of time values in WMDS.

All times shall be encoded using ISO 8601 time format. A time-zone designator must be supplied for all times. If the time is given as UTC then the time zone designator is 'Z' e.g.
2016-12-25T12:00Z
For times given in a local (non UTC) time the time zone designator shall be expressed as an offset from UTC using plus or minus offsets.
For example, the following date times are all the same moment in time:
2016-12-25T10:00Z (10am, timezone is UTC)
2016-12-25T14:00+04:00 (2pm, timezone is UTC + 4 hours)
2016-12-25T06:00-04:00 (6am, timezone is UTC -4 hours)

XML encodings of FacilityLog shall conform to the XML form for FacilityLog specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of Equipment.
Equipment should be used to describe the equipment (instruments) used to make observations.
Equipment may contain sub-equipment. However this is not yet supported in OSCAR (2016).
XML encodings of Equipment shall conform to the XML form for Equipment specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

The value for geopositioningMethod, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/GeopoistioningMethod.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of EquipmentLog.
The purpose of the EquipmentLog is to record calibration/control checks and maintenance undertaken on the equipment.
Where a log entry is a ControlCheckReport, the value of standardType shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ControlStandardType.
Log entries in a EquipmentLog shall describe control checks or maintenance of the Equipment and shall conform to the XML forms for ControlCheckReport or MaintenanceReport in the WMDR XML Schema.
Where a log entry is a ControlCheckReport, the value of checkLocation shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ControlLocation.

http://def.wmo.int/wmdr/2017/req/equipment/equipment-log-entries-control-result Where a log entry is a ControlCheckReport, the value of controlCheckResult shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ControlResult.

XML encodings of EquipmentLog shall conform to the XML form for EquipmentLog specified in the WMDR XML Schema.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.
This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of OM-Observation, which is referred to as an observation segment in WIGOS.

XML encodings of OM_Observation in WIGOS shall use O&M Spatial Sampling Features to describe the om:featureOfInterest as a feature with geometry describing the geometric location or range of the observations.
XML encodings of OM_Observation shall conform to the XML form for OM_Observation specified in ISO 19156 O&M XML schema.
XML encodings of OM_Observation in WIGOS shall use the WIGOS Process type to describe the om:procedure.
The value for om:observedProperty (observed variable) shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ObservedVariable
XML encodings of OM_Observation in WIGOS shall use the WIGOS ResultSet type to describe the om:result.
Each OM_Observation should describe the observation of a different observed variable (e.g. humidity, air temperature) from a station/facility.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of Process.
The Process has several sub-components: Sampling, Reporting, Processing, Deployment.
XML encodings of Process shall conform to the XML form for Process specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of Sampling.
Sampling describes the sampling used for observations. It is part of the Process.
XML encodings of Sampling shall conform to the XML form for Sampling specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

The value for samplingStrategy, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdsSamplingStrategy.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of Processing.
Processing describes the processing done on observations (post-sampling). It is part of the Process.
XML encodings of Processing shall conform to the XML form for Processing specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

The value(s) for observingMethod shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ObservingMethod.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of Reporting.
Reporting describes how the observations are reported. It is part of the Process.

The value for uom, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/Unit.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value for dataUseConstraints, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/DataPolicy.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value for dataFormat, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/DataFormat.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value for referenceTime, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ReferenceTime.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value for levelOfData, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/LevelOfData.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.
XML encodings of Reporting shall conform to the XML form for Reporting specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

The value for temporalReportingTimeStampMeaning, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/TimeStampMeaning.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

This requirements class contains a set of rules applicable to the XML encoding of Deployment.
Deployment describes how the equipment is configured for observations. It is part of the Process. One process may contain multiple deployments for different time periods (e.g. a sensor may be changed warranting a new Deployment description).

The value(s) for sourceOfObservation shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/SourceOfObservation.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value(s) for applicationArea shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/ApplicationArea.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value for exposure, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/Exposure.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.
XML encodings of Deployment shall conform to the XML form for Deployment specified in the WMDR XML Schema.

The value for representativeness, if supplied, shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/Representativeness
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.

The value for instrumentOperatingStatus shall be taken from the code table published online at http://codes.wmo.int/common/wmdr/InstrumentOperatingStatus.
This codelist is also described in the WIGOS Metadata Standard, Chapter VII.
